content: Great kids game! I loved this game when my kids were little. I just discovered it on Google play for my great nieces and nephews. As far as I can tell it is just as great as the previous PC version. The only downside I can see is that the graphic animals mouths keep moving long after they have stopped talking.
i love the game
Works fine on both my LG G7 and my son's Chromebook.
Quality sucks
It doesn't work, when I press start it opens up to some boot screen telling me to type exit to enter the game but then it wouldn't let me type it in to start it
Played straight through in one sitting without any glitches. 90s nostalgia at its finest.
Takes me way back when I were yong and still enjoy

I used to play this on my home computer in 1996 when I was three and I thought I would never get to play these games again. I am absolutely floored at how easy it was to find this game, install it, and play this on my phone, and how good it looked. Thank you so much for this window into my childhood.

Loved it! Ran with no issues for me. Thank you for allowing me to replay my childhood again, this was very nostalgic! It's amazing how much quicker you get through these games as an adult :)

I did not enjoy the game as much as I did when I was a child. It took me about thirty minutes to one hour to finish the entire game including play around in the mini games I would like a refund as Sure I played the game but I do not think less than an hour of game play is worth five dollars plus I had trouble starting the app I had to click on the tiny HE icon at the very very start of opening the app or it would keep saying checking license.  In all I love the game and recommend it to be played by any kid but I do not believe it is worth five dollars maybe one or two max.

The developer's advice was to reinstall it and contact Apple (seriously HE?) for a refund if that didn't work.  So, thank you Google for my refund. I strongly advise against this or any HE product.

Good: Exactly as I remember it. All the silly sounds and tics bring back waves of memories.     Bad: It won't open the first time it's clicked. Must click on icon at least 20-30 times before it works. And during gameplay the screen sometime fragments into three pieces, but this is fixed by pressing the running apps button and going back to the game. Nothings perfect, but this game is still awesome!
